==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whey
<hw>Whey</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>hw⟦ae⟧g</ets>;
cf. D. <ets>wei</ets>, <ets>hui</ets>, Fries. <ets>weye</ets>, LG.
<ets>wey</ets>, <ets>waje</ets>. ]</ety> <def>The serum, or watery part,
of milk, separated from the more thick or coagulable part, esp. in the
process of making cheese.</def> <note>In this process, the thick part is
called <contr>curd</contr>, and the thin part <ex>whey</ex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whey cure</ent>⟦br⟧
